22/12/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- US President George Bush has congratulated Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on the EU's decision to launch accession talks with Ankara, the White House announced Tuesday (21 December).
The president said during a phone conversation that this would strengthen Turkey's relations with Europe and the United States.
The two leaders also discussed the January elections in Iraq, as well as the need to bolster security co-operation among Washington, Ankara and Baghdad.
Representatives of the three governments are to meet in Turkey to discuss the matter.
(AFP, NTV, Anadolu Agency - 21/12/04)
